==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nauseate
<hw>Nau"se*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Nauseated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Nauseating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>nauseare</ets>, <ets>nauseatum</ets>, fr. <ets>nausea</ets>. See
<er>Nausea</er>.]</ety> <def>To become squeamish; to feel nausea; to
turn away with disgust.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nauseate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nauseate
<hw>Nau"se*ate</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To affect with
nausea; to sicken; to cause to feel loathing or disgust.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To sicken at; to reject with disgust; to
loathe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The patient <qex>nauseates</qex> and loathes wholesome foods.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackmore.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nauseation</ent>⟦br⟧
